  <description type="morphology">Stems erect, ascending, or decumbent-ascending, 1–13 dm, minutely puberulent, glabrate, or glabrous basally. Leaf blades grayish or bluish green, linear, 3–10 × 0.1–1(–1.3) cm, surfaces glabrous or glandular-pubescent. Inflorescences of single involucres in axils, or terminal, well branched with ± well-defined main axis; fruiting involucres 5–10(–15) mm, crosswalls of peduncle hairs usually pale. Perianth white to deep rose-pink.</description>
